author: Times-News
title: Elon falls in OT in women's soccer
text: Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 12:35 AM Updated at 12:36 AM Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 12:35 AM Updated at 12:36 AM PHILADELPHIA — Drexel’s Vanessa Kara scored the game-winning goal in the 104th minute as the Dragons defeated visiting Elon 2-1 in double overtime in Colonial Athletic Association women’s soccer Sunday afternoon at Vidas Field. Elon (9-5-2 overall, 1-4-1 CAA) struck first when Grace Bennett scored her first goal of the season at the 58th minute mark. Kara answered 11 minutes later with a goal for Drexel (8-8, 2-5). Drexel outshot the Phoenix 30-7. Taylor Mohr stopped seven shots for the Phoenix. Eve Badana registered the Dragons’ lone save. By Times-News
